We had our first completely vegan Christmas, with the menu planned by us alone, and it was very peaceful and loving. In total, we had 8 dishes and 1 vegan red wine (ð§you would be surprised most red wine isn't vegan). 
.
ðFood & drink: 
1. Prime Roots Foods vegan roast chicken 
2. Impossible Foods lasagna w/ homemade truffle cheese, 'meat' sauce + mozzarella cheese 
3. Beyond Meat sausage stuffing 
4. Cheeseboard: Homemade chive cheddar cheese, blue cheese, seedy crackers, Grissini, apricot jam & pear butter 
5. Garlic Brussel sprouts ð§ 
6. Pear salad 
7. Red fruit sorbet 
8. Blueberry pie ð¥§ 
9. Vegan red red wine made me feel so fine 
.
ðRecipes: 
Most of them are from my culinary classes. 
Lasagna is created by Sicilian Paul. 
Brussels sprouts and pear salad from Minimalist Baker. 
The Beyond Meat sausage stuffing was the highlight of the night - you can find this incredible recipe on the Beyond Meat website. 

ð¦â: Vegan fur coat 
I am obsessed with this @ragandbone vegan fur, which probably has the best quality I have seen in faux fur and fur. The texture is very fluffy and smooth. The oversized style gives it more "attitude" and personality. More importantly, no animals got skinned alive, anally electrocuted, or beaten to death.
